{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, with 30,000 segmented cells with an average of 30 detected transcripts and 20 unique genes per cell (Supplementary Fig. 6d, e, empty rate <0.25% with 15 empty barcodes), the kidney DART-FISH data was annotated to cortical and altered cell types as identified in the single-cell kidney atlas 73 (Fig.",
    "4c, Supplementary Fig. 6f, Supplementary Fig.",
    "7, Methods).",
    "These annotated cell types were of the expected relative proportions and showed strong and specific differential expression of corresponding marker genes (Fig. 4d, Supplementary Fig.",
    "6f, Supplementary Fig. 8a)."
  ]
}